    <item>
      <title>Eclipsed With You</title>
      <author> Fallen4Freedom </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1810341/eclipsed-with-you/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1810341-eclipsed-with-you/chapter/1810351/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">4d54bdd2f4be4d95005ee4c0fda2957b33c1eb9b</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 22 Aug 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Forensic Investigator Reyna Solis thought that the death of Dante Algarin was just an easy closed case. That is until weird happenings begin at The Motherlode that puts its owner, Raphael De Leon in peril. Can Reyna solve this mystery before anyone else succumbs to the curtain call?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1810341-eclipsed-with-you/chapter/1810351/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Prologue&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;They say the night is young when one walks down the St. Mary Strip. The bars and clubs lined up were a delight to the hundreds that would flock to it on an almost nightly basis. One club, however, stuck out from the rest. Its golden neon sign shone brightly against what looked like a giant rock with a red carpet lining its mine-like entrance. This club was The Mother Lode, and behind its glass doors was a small, plump figure exiting from the interior lobby. He was a horned lizard with a golden hue, his namesake features tipped with a soft magenta. His curly brown hair extended to his lower back, nearly reaching his short tail. His attire, a contrast to the bright and flashy lights, was a basic white tank top and a pair of comfortable gray sweats.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;‘Another night, another dollar.’ he thinks to himself as he locks the main entrance.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;He then heads over to the employee parking lot to fetch his custom solar cycle to go home. But he hears a scream. Before he’s able to process what’s going on, he dashes towards the source while praying that he isn’t too late. Rounding the corner, he stops dead in his tracks as a look of dread bleeds onto his face. The body he sees is curled up along the cold pavement by the root of a crepe myrtle tree. And as faint as the light is, he’s able to recognize the shape belonging to a familiar opossum.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Dante!"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;He rushes over to his friend, fidgeting in his gym bag for something to stop the bleeding. When he reaches her, the sight is much more ghastly to behold than he initially imagined. Under Dante's hand is a deep slash at the front of her neck, gushing with so much blood it seeps through her thin, pale fingers and onto the concrete beneath. The horned lizard frantically burrows deeper into his bag until finally, he finds a hand towel and promptly applies pressure to the wound with one hand and dialing emergency services with the other. He waits with bated breath as the phone begins to connect.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;______________________________________________________________________&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"After about five minutes, the ambulance arrives," he states, "but unfortunately she passed away not too long after."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The hospital lobby, though a stale white, is decorated with streams of crystalized colors hanging from the ceiling like stalactites. Though filled with many families waiting for their loved ones, his focus was fixed on Detective Kori Daniels, a puma with long, black braided hair, dressed in a green turtle neck sweater underneath a brown leather jacket, complete with a pair of blue jeans. She listened intently to him as she took notes of the incident the night before.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Thank you, Mr. De Leon." She said. "I do apologize for your loss, but you've informed the hospital staff of her... 'Condition'?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The horned lizard simply nodded in response. With the statement made, the puma detective stood up and pocketed her notebook in her jacket. She once again turned to the horned lizard before setting off towards the exit.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Your cooperation means a lot to us, Raphael." She smiles. "We'll be sure to conduct a thorough investigation of the crime scene. I hope you'll assist us again when the time comes."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Oh... Of course." Raphael replied.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/805985109458026566/1403449180671836231/crimson_chokehold.png?ex=68a963a7&amp;amp;is=68a81227&amp;amp;hm=caef5bbc670decc5af914851dab0959d70e28d2c09d393467c7c93581e41a549&amp;amp;" alt="" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After Kori exits, Raphael holds his face in his hands. Though he had a calm exterior during the interview, his mind was still racing from the initial sight of his friend gasping for air while under the crimson chokehold. But what good would that do for her? He had to know who and why they would target her specifically. The horned lizard slowly stood up, waiting for the call to seek justice for one of his closest friends. He swore it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
